Looking at my available digits [6, 0, 9, 5], I can use either 0 or 5 as the last digit to make the number divisible by 5.

To create the largest possible number, I should:
1. Use the largest available digit as the last digit (which would be 5)
2. Arrange the remaining digits in descending order for the rest of the number
